tip.text: Great pizza and homemade pasta. Not cheap, but worth it.
Great Balinese farbrics. Pricey but authentic and beautiful.
Still one of the best specialty coffee roasters in Hong Kong.
Decent coffee, relaxed atmosphere, good music. The pricey scones where a bit dry though.
Simple, authentic Yunnan street food - the spicy Kunming noodles with minced pork are great! Low-key atmosphere. I'll be back.
Oh no, they changed the kimchi supplier! Gone is one of the best kimchi spots in town. The new stuff is sweet and watery and not at all as good.
Great Italian food, awesome flavors, fresh ingredients, nicely presented. Well done.
